<br>
I just wanted to know if lighter weapons equal less stamina loss. Right now I have a Lammy and Centi SS and having problems in long fights with stamina. I don't know if it's due to the centi being like 5 wt but the Lammy is pretty low. Would I be better off with getting rid of the centi and buying something lighter? I currently have over 200 STA from crusty armor so I dont think that's the problem. Any help is appreciated. Thanks!<br>
<br>
Kazmilan Shinkicker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=norpin>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 10:42:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4592.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does a lighter weapon = less STA loss?</span><hr size=1> Yes, a lighter weapon will not make you lose as much stamina per swing IIRC.  If you have that much stamina then I'm surprised you care.  Do you need to jump that often? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 628<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 10:42:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4592.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does a lighter weapon = less STA loss?</span><hr size=1> Yes it does.  However, if your stamina is over 100 is has been shown that stamina loss is irrelevant. <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
