31 Wood Elf Druid</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=friedrick>Friedrick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 10:57:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4592.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does a lighter weapon = less STA loss?</span><hr size=1> To answer your question, yes a lighter weapon will have less of a stamina drain on you than a heavier weapon.  Just as a faster weapon will drain it quicker than a slower one of a given weight.<br>
<br>
Other than not being able to jump why do you care if you run out of stamina though?  At 200 stamina you should suffer no loss in attack speed even when the bar is drained.  During prolonged fights you will be hard pressed to not drain your stamina bar.  I currently run with anywhere from 202 to 265 stamina depending on buffs and swinging ancient prismatic battlehammer (1.5 weight) and priceless velium sword (2.5 weight).  For prolonged fighting my stamina will drain out.<br>
<br>
We are not casters, we are warriors.  We continue to dish out and take beatings when others grow weary and cannot sustain the pace.  Be glad for this.<br>
<br>
Friedrick - 63rd Warlord on Tunare Server<br>
